doctype html
html
	head
		meta(charset='utf-8')
		meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0')
		meta(name='description', content='A tool to check creative and technical writing for potential improvements.')
		
		title Writing Check by Tyler Walters

		link(rel='stylesheet', href='http://yui.yahooapis.com/pure/0.5.0/pure-min.css')
		<!--[if lte IE 8]> 
		link(rel='stylesheet', href='http://yui.yahooapis.com/pure/0.5.0/grids-responsive-old-ie-min.css') 
		<![endif]-->
		<!--[if gt IE 8]><!--> 
		link(rel='stylesheet', href='http://yui.yahooapis.com/pure/0.5.0/grids-responsive-min.css') 
		<!--<![endif]-->
		link(rel='stylesheet', href='http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jqueryui/1.10.4/themes/smoothness/jquery-ui.css')
		link(rel='stylesheet', href='css/style.css')
		link(rel='stylesheet', href='http://netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.1.0/css/font-awesome.min.css')
		link(rel='stylesheet', href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Merriweather:400,700,400italic')

	body
		div.pure-menu.pure-menu-open.pure-menu-horizontal.pure-menu-fixed
			a.pure-menu-heading(href='') 
				h1 Writing Check

			ul
				li.pure-menu-selected
					a(href='#check') 
						i.fa.fa-pencil 
						| &nbsp; Check Writing
				li
					a(href='#definitions') 
						i.fa.fa-book 
						| &nbsp; Definitions
				li
					a(href='#about') 
						i.fa.fa-info 
						| &nbsp; About

		div.pure-g.main-content#check
			div.pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-2.input-column
				div.content-box
					
					p Enter your text copy:

					form#writing-check-form.pure-form.pure-form.stacked
						fieldset
							textarea#writing-check-input.writing-check-input.pure-input-1(name='writing-check-input', required)

							div.pure-g
								div.pure-u-1.pure-u-sm-1-2.check-box-options
									label.pure-checkbox.adverb(for='check-adverb')
										input#check-adverb(type='checkbox', value='adverb')
										i.fa.fa-question-circle.fa-inverse.pull-right(title='Check for adverbs that could be replaced with stronger verbs.')
										| &nbsp; Adverbs
									label.pure-checkbox.filler-words(for='check-filler')
										input#check-filler(type='checkbox', value='fillerWords')
										i.fa.fa-question-circle.fa-inverse.pull-right(title='Check for adverbs that could be replaced with stronger verbs.')
										| &nbsp; Filler Words
									label.pure-checkbox.passive-voice(for='check-passive')
										input#check-passive(type='checkbox', value='passiveVoice')
										i.fa.fa-question-circle.fa-inverse.pull-right(title='Check for adverbs that could be replaced with stronger verbs.')
										| &nbsp; Passive Voice

								div.pure-u-1.pure-u-sm-1-2.check-box-options
									label.pure-checkbox.lexical-illusions(for='check-lexical')
										input#check-lexical(type='checkbox', value='lexicalIllusions')
										i.fa.fa-question-circle.fa-inverse.pull-right(title='Check for adverbs that could be replaced with stronger verbs.')
										| &nbsp; Lexical Illusions
									label.pure-checkbox.misused-words(for='check-misused')
										input#check-misused(type='checkbox', value='misusedWords')
										i.fa.fa-question-circle.fa-inverse.pull-right(title='Check for adverbs that could be replaced with stronger verbs.')
										| &nbsp; Common Misused Words
									label.pure-checkbox.pronoun(for='pronoun')
										input#pronoun(type='checkbox', value='pronoun')
										i.fa.fa-question-circle.fa-inverse.pull-right(title='Check for adverbs that could be replaced with stronger verbs.')
										| &nbsp; Pronouns

							button#writing-check-button.pure-button.pure-button-primary Submit

			div.pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-2.output-column
				div.content-box

					div#writing-check-output
						p Checked text copy will go here.

		div.pure-g.definitions#definitions
			div.pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-3.definitions-list
				div.content-box

					ul
						li.adverb Adverbs
						li.filler-words Filler Words
						li.passive-voice Passive Voice
						li.lexical-illusions Lexical Illusions
						li.misused-words Commonly Misused Words
						li.pronoun Pronouns

			div.pure-u-1.pure-u-md-2-3.definitions-description
				div.content-box

					div.adverb-description
						h2 Adverbs
						ul
							li -ly
						p Adverbs are used to modify another word. Adverbs are often unneeded. The adverb and the word it modifies can be replaced by a stronger word or the adverb can be ommitted without losing anything.

					div.filler-word-description
						h2 Filler Words
						ul
							li very, several, many, most, few, vast, just, quite, often, various, a number of
						p These words can usually be ommitted. They often do not add anything of value to the writing other than word count. Ommitting them can tighten up your writing.

					div.passive-voice-description
						h2 Passive Voice
						ul
							li (is, isn't, are, aren't, am, am not, was, wasn't, were, weren't, had, hadn't, has been, have been, had been, will be, being) + past particle
						p These words can be indicators of passive voice. Passive voice occurs when you make the object of action into the subject of a sentence. 
						p Passive voice is not always bad but it can affect the clarity or weaken the impact of a sentence. It can often be replaced with an active sentence structure to improve the writing. 
						p Further reading: 
							a(href='http://writingcenter.unc.edu/handouts/passive-voice/') Passive Voice at UNC Writing Center

					div.lexical-illusions-description
						h2 Lexical Illusions
						ul
							li duplicate words
						p Lexical illusions are words duplicate words at a line break that are often missed when reading or editing copy because our brains will automatically ignore the second instance.

					div.misused-words-description
						h2 Commonly Misused Words
						ul
							li their, they're, there, your, you're, its, it's, whose, who's
						p These words are often misused. Double check them to make sure you used the correct word in each case. 

					div.pronoun-description
						h2 Pronouns
						ul
							li he, she, it
						p This test highlights pronouns so you can make sure there are not too many too close toghether and that it is clear who or what each one is referring to.

		script(src='http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.1/jquery.min.js')
		script(src='http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jqueryui/1.10.4/jquery-ui.min.js')
		script(src='js/script.js')

		